# DoMo CLI
DoMo is a Docker Monitoring Command Line Tool which collects the most important metrics running docker containers.

## Installation
You can install domo with 
`pip install domo`

## Prerequisites
DoMo collects metrics by sending a query request to Prometheus Server. To collect docker container metrics(Memory/Disk/CPU usage) and monitor app logs, the following prerequisites should be satisfied:
1. Docker Engine is running
2. Prometheus server is running in http://localhost:9090/
3. cAdvisor and Grok Exporter are integrated in Prometheus
## How to use
1. type `domo` to get an overview of all commands
![img.png](img.png)
2. Use `domo list-containers` to get id and name of all running containers
   ![img_1.png](img_1.png)
3. Use `domo container <container_name>/<container_id>` to list container metrics
4. Use `domo logs` to show the latestError information in app log file


   

